 <br /> Chicago Sun-Times, January 31, 2007, "UIC team ready to get medieval on spammers," by technology columnist Sandra Guy.
<p />
First Business (appears daily on over 150 television stations around the U.S. and overseas), January 11, 2007, Interviewed to discuss Apple's new iPhone.
<p />
New York Times, September 17, 2006, Editorial &ndash; &ldquo;Legacy Admissions,&rdquo; by Peter C. Nelson.
<p />
Pioneer Press (appeared in 57 suburban Pioneer Press newspapers), August 3, 2006, &ldquo;Computer Science study falls in U.S.,&rdquo; by Karen Shoffner.
<p />
Chicago Tribune, May 15, 2005, Letter to Editor &ndash; &ldquo;Remain Competitive,&rdquo; by Pete Nelson.
<p />
<a href="http://logos.cs.uic.edu/recruit/AdvantagesOfDiversity.htm" target="_top">Chicago Sun-Times, April 1, 2006,</a> Commentary Essay &ndash; &ldquo;Don&rsquo;t Overlook diversity when it&rsquo;s time to pick a college,&rdquo; by Pete Nelson.
<p />
Redeye, Friday Feb. 6, 2004, Inside Cover, &ldquo;Honoring the Crash Test Genius,&rdquo; by Chris <span class="twikiNewLink"><a href="https://www.cs.uic.edu/bin/edit/PeterNelson/McNamera?topicparent=PeterNelson.MediaQuotesInterviews;nowysiwyg=0" rel="nofollow" title="McNamera (this topic does not yet exist; you can create it)">McNamera</a></span>.<br /> <br /> Daily Herald, Jan. 21, 2002, &ldquo;Illinois gets top rating for tech use,&rdquo; by Daschell M. Phillips.<br /> <br /> Chicago Sun-Times, January 8, 2002, SECTION: FINANCIAL; Pg. 12, &ldquo;Dot-com crash victims flocking back to college,&rdquo; by Brenda Warner Rotzoll.<br /> <br /> Chicago Tribune, November 26, 2001, SECTION: BUSINESS; Pg. 3, &ldquo; Wireless connections touted as DSL alternative,&rdquo; by Jon Van.<br /> <br /> CBS Channel 2 10pm News, July 30, 2001, &ldquo;Code Red Virus Alert.&rdquo;<br /> <br /> San Diego Union-Tribune, July 8, 2001, Sunday, Pg. A-1, &ldquo;Artificial intelligence is alive in laboratories, works on Web; Computers thinking like humans nothing like movie,&rdquo; by Jeff Meredith.<br /> <br /> Chicago Tribune, July 2, 2001, Monday, SECTION: BUSINESS; Pg. 3, &ldquo;A.I. forms already in use; Northwestern, UIC labs focus on convenience,&rdquo; by Jeff Meredith. Chicago Tribune, July 29, 1999, Thursday, Frontpage Headline: &ldquo;GAME WARY; RETAILERS ARE REFUSING TO SELL SOME TITLES AS CONCERN ABOUT THE EFFECTS OF VIOLENCE GROWS.; STORES OPPOSE CHECKING IDS,&rdquo; by Susan Chandler.<br /> <br /> Crain's Chicago Business, November 8, 1993, Pg. R5, &ldquo;Smart car technology heads into suburbs,&rdquo; by Bill <span class="twikiNewLink"><a href="https://www.cs.uic.edu/bin/edit/PeterNelson/McDowel?topicparent=PeterNelson.MediaQuotesInterviews;nowysiwyg=0" rel="nofollow" title="McDowel (this topic does not yet exist; you can create it)">McDowel</a></span>. </div><!-- /patternTopic-->
